    <instructions>Marination for chicken korma recipe
1. Marinate chicken with 3 tbsps yogurt, 1 tbsp ginger garlic paste, ¼ tsp turmeric, ½ tsp salt, 1 to 1¼ tsp red chili powder and ¾ to 1 tsp garam masala.  
2. Cover this and set aside until needed. 
Make onion paste
1. Heat a pan with 1½ to 2 tbsps oil and add 2 cardamoms.  
2. Add sliced onions and fry them evenly until golden brown.  
3. Next add cashews and almonds. Cool these completely.  
4. Later add the cooled onions and nuts to a blender jar along with yogurt. 
5. Make a smooth paste of these. Set this aside. 
How to make chicken korma
1. To the same pan, add 1 tsp oil and heat it.

2. Saute whole spices – bay leaf, cinnamon stick, cloves and cardamom in oil for a min.  
3. Add green chilli and marinated chicken.  
4. Fry on a medium heat until the raw smell of ginger garlic paste goes away. 
5. Then add the onion curd paste. Pour ¾ cup water and mix well. 
6. Add salt, coriander powder and garam masala. If desired you can also add more chili powder for color. 
7. Mix well. Cover and cook on a low flame until chicken is cooked to tender. 
8. Cook further till the gravy reaches a desired consistency. If it is too thick then pour some hot water to bring it to consistency. 
9. Garnish with coriander leaves.

10. Serve chicken korma with plain basmati rice, naan, roti or paratha.</instructions>
